# Lychee ignore list (URL regexes). Keep this lean — the point of the link
# checker is to catch real rot, so only exclude sources that produce known
# false positives in CI.

# npm's web UI (npmjs.com/package/...) returns HTTP 403 to automated clients
# because of bot protection, which is a false positive in CI. Whether a package
# actually exists is validated by the CI `npm pack --workspaces --dry-run` job
# and by the npm registry, not by scraping the website.
https://www\.npmjs\.com/

# Local dev servers referenced in quickstart snippets.
^https?://localhost
^https?://127\.0\.0\.1
